  "title": "Aesthetic Beauty Therapist / Clinician (Medical Aesthetics))",
  "description": "<p>As an established leading aesthetic chain, ClearSK manages the award-winning ClearSK® chain of medical-aesthetics clinics in Singapore, Shanghai & Hangzhou and Kuala Lumpur.</p><p>We are looking for <strong>passionate</strong> and <strong>motivated</strong> individuals who possess <strong>drive</strong> and <strong>ambition</strong> to join our dynamic team today! Discover yourself through our various career progression programs and carve your own future with us!</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>To perform skin, body and/or hair analysis to customers</li><li>To provide valuable advices to customers in a professional manner</li><li>To recommend suitable treatment packages to customers</li><li>To perform course treatments, not limited to skin, body or hair</li><li>To attend to incoming calls and arrange appointments</li><li>To be responsible for own appointment bookings</li><li>Daily housekeeping and upkeep of machine conditions</li><li>Ensure condiments and accessories for customers are replenished at all times</li><li>Other administrative work as assigned by branch managers or management</li></ul><p><strong>Role Requirement</strong></p><ul><li>Min. requirement of Diploma or equivalent</li><li>Good personal hygiene and well-groomed</li><li>Proficient in English communication and writing.</li><li>Ability to read, write, and converse in Chinese will be an added advantage as liaising with Chinese customers.</li><li>Willing to work retail hours and weekends</li><li>Willing to travel</li><li>Prior experiences in aesthetic / healthcare sector will be an advantage</li><li>Preferred qualification in \"para-medical science\" degree /diploma in nutrition, food science, biomedical, physiotherapy, pharmacy.</li><li>Cidesco / CIBTEC / ITEC / NSRS / NITEC Spa and Aesthetic Therapy, WSQ will be an advantage</li><li>An independent and initiative individual who plays well in team</li><li>Able to handle Service & Sales (S&S) orientated environment</li><li>Comfortable in handling IT systems and devices (i.e. Laptop, printer, mobile) – you will need to use them daily</li></ul><p><strong>Benefits</strong></p><ul><li>Career Progression</li><li>5 Days work week + Service & Sales incentives + allowances</li><li>Convenient working locations</li><li>Medical benefits</li><li>Product and services benefits</li><li>OJT provided</li></ul><p><strong>Application process:</strong></p><p><strong>Should you wish to be considered for shortlisting, please complete the attached Google Form at the link below prior to submitting your application:</strong></p><p>https://forms.gle/BANHb1kAYwBY7k6D8</p><p><br /></p><p>Please be advised that only candidates who have completed the form and are subsequently shortlisted will be notified.</p>",
